[...]

Also check out marine suppliers that cater to commercial fishermen and boatbuilders, or peruse the ads in 'National Fisherman' and similar publications.

There are lots of companies on the coasts that custom build plastic or welded aluminum tanks.  You can have whatever plumbing, fittings, internal baffling, etc. you want.  

Besides commercial stuff, they do plenty of business with pleasure boaters that want added fuel storage.  Those projects often require all sorts of peculiar shapes to fit into available spaces below decks.

FWIW...
